  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Leaflet</ab>
      <ab subtype="creation" type="lido:event">
        <date>1932 after</date>
      </ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The framed leaflet produced by the ‘Kasina’ cinema advertises the ‘newest Ufa-hit’,‘Pobednik’ (the Serbo-Croatian translation of the original German film title ‘Der Sieger’), starring Hans Albers and Käthe von Nagy. The main song hits were recorded by the ‘Comedian Harmonists’ and Willi Domgraf-Fassbaender.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The film was directed by Hans Hinrich and Paul Martin and was released in 1932. ‘Ufa’ stands for ‘Universal Film AG’, Germany’s biggest film production company at that time. The ‘Kasina’ cinema was founded in 1911 in Belgrade.</ab>
